Publishing inventions and technologies on Appropedia is a version of open sourcing [[intellectual property]]. There is a growth in the concept of '''Open source patents'''. For example, the [http://www.openinventionnetwork.com/ Open Invention Network] is a type of patent pooling arrangement which seeks to defend the [[Linux]] System from [[patents]]. The concept of [[open source technology]] is in its infancy and needs considerable work.

There is already considerable work being done on [[open patents]]{{w|open patents}} and the [http://www.patentcommons.org/ Patent Commons] has been created to assist in open software development.

